						<summary>

						<p>On a slab set up in front of the temple of Uḷivi Basappa.</p>						

						<p>Jagadēkamalla II, 1139 A.D.</p>						

						<p>The inscription is partially damaged. The extant date portion contains the details, [Siddhārthi], Uttarāyaṇa-saṅkrānti, Monday. In the cyclic year cited, which fell within the regnal period of the king, Uttarāyaṇa-saṅkrānti occurred on December 25, Monday, 1139 A.D.</p>						

						<p>The record registers a gift the details of which are lost.</p>						

						</summary>
